The paper discusses the use of machine learning to make design decisions for constraint solvers, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The case study specifically focuses on the alldifferent constraint, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper also discusses the implementation of the machine learning system as part of a general-purpose constraint solver, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
